text: Dustin M. Johnson (born September 30, 1976) is an American politician. He is the U.S. Representative for South Dakota's at-large congressional district since 2019. He is a member of the Republican Party. He was South Dakota Public Utilities Commissioner from 2005 to 2011. ==References== Category:1976 births Category:Living people Category:United States representatives from South Dakota Category:People from Pierre, South Dakota Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians Category:Businesspeople from South Dakota
